085c5f9acd53dcaf7e9d1dad3e8ed85a.filed_by: Rural County Representatives of California,Bioenergy Association of California
085c5f9acd53dcaf7e9d1dad3e8ed85a.description: NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION OF THE BIOENERGY ASSOCIATION OF CALIFORNIA AND THE RURAL COUNTY REPRESENTATIVES OF CALIFORNIA Pursuant to Rules 8.2 and 8.4 of Commissions Rules of Practice and Procedure, the Bioenergy Association of California (BAC) and the Rural County Representatives of California (RCRC) hereby give notice of an ex parte communication that occurred via WebEx on Wednesday, January 29, 2025, at 1pm.  The ex parte communication was a meeting between Commissioner John Reynolds energy advisor, Carolyn Chen, BACs Executive Director, Julia Levin, and RCRC Policy Advocates John Kennedy and Leigh Kammerich.  The other meeting participants (who are not parties to this Rulemaking) included Thomas Jordan (CEO, Scotts Valley Energy Corp, Scotts Valley Band of Pomo Indians), Bruce Springsteen (Air Quality Engineer for Placer County Air Pollution Control District), and Greg Kester (Director of Renewable Resource Programs, California Association of Sanitation Agencies).

5650b9bcf6ea8906088277f90531fc19.filed_by: Rural County Representatives of California,Bioenergy Association of California
5650b9bcf6ea8906088277f90531fc19.description: ADVANCE NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION OF THE BIOENERGY ASSOCIATION OF CALIFORNIA AND THE RURAL COUNTY REPRESENTATIVES OF CALIFORNIA Pursuant to Rules 8.2 and 8.4 of Commissions Rules of Practice and Procedure, the Bioenergy Association of California (BAC) and the Rural County Representatives of California (RCRC) hereby give advance notice of an ex parte communication to take place on Wednesday, January 29, 2025, at 1pm.  The communication will be a meeting via WebEx with Commissioner John Reynolds staff to discuss issues related to the BioMAT program.  The meeting participants are expected to be Maria Sotero (Commissioner Reynolds energy advisor), Bruce Springsteen (Air Quality Engineer for Placer County Air Pollution Control District), John Kennedy and Leigh Kammerich (Policy Advocates, RCRC), Sarah Deslauriers (Director of Air, Climate, and Energy Programs, California Association of Sanitation Agencies), Thomas Jordan (CEO, Scotts Valley Energy Corp), and Julia Levin (Executive Director, BAC).  Two of the meeting participants, BAC and RCRC, are parties in this Rulemaking.
